The man was apparently attempting to intervene in the robbery of informal traders in the area. CAPE TOWN Western Cape police say that a man has been killed in Delft after he attempted to intervene in stopping robbers targeting informal traders.The 32-year-old man was shot and killed when he confronted three suspects.The trio reportedly robbed five stalls in Delft's main road earlier this week.The police's Andre Traut says: The circumstances are being investigated after the man was shot and killed on Wednesday. No one has been arrested as yet. (Edited by Tamsin Wort)